article.headline: Boise St. 83, San Jose St. 64
article.story: BOISE, Idaho (AP) -- Eric Lane pushed his career scoring total past 1,000 points with 22 points and, Reggie Larry added 16 points and five blocked shots to lead Boise State to an 83-64 Western Athletic Conference victory over San Jose State Thursday night. The Broncos (16-10, 8-5) won their 10th straight game over San Jose State (4-23, 3-11). Boise State set a school record with 12 blocked shots. Lane scored 14 of his points in the first eight minutes, hitting 5 of 7 from the field, including 4 for 6 from 3-point range, putting the Broncos ahead 25-12. He failed to score the rest of the first half and Boise State led 45-34 at halftime. The Broncos put the Spartans out of range 62-42 with 15:25 left when Lane scored six straight points in the span of 50 seconds as their full-court press forced three Spartans' turnovers. Menelik Barbary kept the Spartans in the game for awhile. He hit 9 of 11 field goals and led his team with 19 points and 10 rebounds. Boise State's Greg Graham recorded his 100th career coaching victory against 74 losses.
